article.description: Gearhart's 31 leads Rice upset of W. Kentucky, 72-68
article.headline: Gearhart's 31 leads Rice upset of W. Kentucky, 72-68
article.linkText: Gearhart's 31 leads Rice upset of W. Kentucky, 72-68
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ky. -- Seth Gearhart scored a career-high 31 points as Rice upset Western Kentucky, 72-68, knocking the Hilltoppers out of sole possession of first place in Conference-USA Saturday night. Gearhart's layup with 2:01 left to play gave the Owls (7-15, 4-6 C-USA) the lead, 66-65, and he pushed it to a three-point lead with a layup off a feed by Marcus Jackson with 1:22 remaining. Gearhart's two free throws with :22 left made it a five-point game and, following Trency Jackson's 3-pointer with :05 to play, Gearhart added two more free throws for the final margin. The Owls shot 59.5 percent from the field, knocking down 25 of 42 shots, including 7 of 17 from distance. The loss was just the third at home for Western Kentucky (16-7, 9-2), which is now tied with Louisiana Tech and Alabama-Birmingham atop the conference standings. Jackson finished with 23 points to lead the Hilltoppers.
